text: Martine Rustøen Skregelid (born July 6, 1999 in Bærum) is a Norwegian artistic gymnast. She represented her country in the 2014 Youth Olympic Games, but did not make any finals. She was also chosen to compete at the first European Games in Baku, along with teammates Solveig Berg and Sofie Bråten, and placed 23rd as a team. In 2017 she became The northern european champion. She is two time national champion and she has won many national titles both as junior and senior.
